# A group of related [[dialects]] of [[Low German]], spoken in northern [[Germany]] and parts of the [[Netherlands]], formerly also in [[Denmark]], [[Poland]], [[Lithuania]], [[Latvia]], [[Estonia]] and [[Kaliningrad]], [[Russia]].

==Usage Notes==
In English texts, p.e. wiktionary, it is often used as a synonym for Low German. This however can be offensive
to speakers of non-Low Saxon dialects of Low German and the Low Germans themselves differentiate strictly between Nordneddersassisch (Low Saxon; Dialectal group) and Nedderdütsch (Low German; the language). The Low Saxon area classically only includes Holland, Lower Saxony and most parts of Sleswik and Holstein.

